social_posts.post_text:
The tragedy 
is many of us 
don't know how 
to forgive ourselves. 
We get stuck in cycles of 
guilt & regret:
"I can't believe I did that."
"I can't believe how capable I am of hurting someone I love."
"I should have known better."
"I'm supposed to be so much better than this."

It's the end 
and the beginning 
of a vicious 
shame cycle. 
And we end up punishing ourselves 
by withdrawing our own love 
from ourselves, 
thinking that will bring justice. 
But it doesn't, does it? 
The cycle never seems to end.

Not until we compassionately 
and wholeheartedly 
forgive ourselves. 

Not an easy thing to do. 

The great news a lot of us would 
forgive ourselves 
if we knew how to. 
Perhaps we were never 
taught how to practice 
consciously being tender 
with ourselves 
until it becomes 
a habit. 
If you are capable of compassion, 
of releasing your feelings of 
anger & resentment 
towards another being, 
then you are capable 
of being compassionate 
towards yourself. 

Forgiveness sets you free.

And there is 
justice from learning 
from your mistakes 
and becoming free.
You are not stuck; 
you have been granted 
the opportunity to know better, 
to grow, 
to live in alignment with who 
you actually want to be. 🤍

———

Morning reflections:
Recognizing 
who 
you 
are 
is one of the most 
important things in life. 

Standing by yourself 
and not bending 
for anyone 
is a task that will 
take you further. 

Stand by your words. 

Listen to others 
but do not let yourself 
be manipulated. 
Take your time to think for yourself. 
And don't be 
fooled by people 
who want to steal 
your light. 

You are your own master. 
Your own teacher and lover. 
You are here to learn and grow. 
Even if you fail 
you have the chance 
to 
do 
it 
again. 
Be your own light in this world. And you will 
shine brighter 
than the sun. 
Nobody can stop you
on your own journey. 👣

Do you, like me, long to wander?
Wanderlust.
That feeling of intense desire, 
an urge of unrelenting potency 
which seemingly pulls 
on every thread 
of your being 
to manifest it as reality. 
A feeling where the border 
between escape & exploration 
becomes a blur.
This is the feeling of wanderlust, 
and it can lead to the 
most life-changing experiences 
of your future. 
It sets my soul ablaze 
and my mind dreaming of
far-off landscapes 
and spontaneous adventures. 
I also know that wanderlust 
can be masking 
a deeper longing 
hidden within. 
I know that my tendency 
to wander has 
a shadow side that often 
stems from brokenness.
I also know, 
though, 
that our places of brokenness 
are also our places of redemption. 
It is not in spite 
of our brokenness 
but because of it 
that we have a message to contribute 
to the world. 
It is like the two sides of a coin,
one does not exist without the other.
But I’ve learned my brokenness stems from longing for home. 
I think I’ve always been searching. 
Longing for home. 
Looking every where I went for, 
home. 
I’ve always stated I’m 
perpetually home sick. 
Always longing 
to go home but 
unsure where home was.
I can say 
for the first time 
I feel I’ve found 
home. 
In this place. 
In this moment. 
In these moments. 
Home. 
It’s here 
It’s now. 
I finally feel home. 
And it’s beyond my wildest dreams. ✨

Do not drown me 
with mediocrity, 
give me passion, 
desire, 
make me 
inhale breaths 
of lust and love 
in the dark hours
that tingle 
down my spine. 🖤
In the midst of destruction I found the grace to begin again ✨

Today’s meditations:

I know we all say this a lot 
but the truth is we 
don’t completely understand 
what other person carries 
right below the surface. 
The weight they carry.
Just because they 
carry it with grace 
does not mean it is not heavy. 
All the silent tears 
that they have cried. 
Or the hard swallows 
just to hold them back. 
The smiles they push through on the hard days. And the laughs they fake for self preservation. 

I feel we all can empathize with silent pain.
My remedy for this is kindness. 
A warm smile. 
A kind thought. 
And encouraging sentiment. 
Hold the door for a stranger. 
Don’t ride the car in front of yours ass. 
Spend 5 minutes in gratitude. 

I am learning this from the loving examples of the remarkable humans in my life 
that show me pain shared 
is truly pain lessen. 
I am learning to become 
all I want to be 
by letting go of 
all I hold on so tightly to. 
I’m learning to step outside 
of myself 
and observe. 
To see the whole story. 
And to shed light to the dark. 
These beautiful souls 
in my life 
showed me 
all I wanted was 
to be loved. 
So they taught me how to love.🤍

A fierce woman is a 
glorious female creature 
whose idea of beauty 
is hinged upon the idea 
that she can change the world 
with each choice, 
each moment, 
and each breath of her life. 
The word beautiful 
serves to encompass 
all areas of 
mind, 
body, 
and soul. 
Beauty is an element that 
guides her actions, 
and her actions are always 
in tune with a foundation of 
morals and convictions 
that come from 
a lifelong appreciation of learning. 
And by learning I don’t mean 
simply reading books 
and burying oneself 
in the depths of the Internet 
searching for all kinds of articles. 
No, learning is the 
creative ability 
to see beyond the surface, 
beyond what is presented to you 
in the mainstream, 
and recognize the power that you have, the power as the beholder. 
A fierce woman is 
not a bystander 
in her own life. 
A fierce woman will use 
her wisdom, 
intuition, 
and imagination 
to exact change 
and choice in the world around her. 🤍

Find someone who pays attention. 
Who runs their fingers 
over your every scar; 
and asks where each one came from. 
Find someone who knows 
how you like your coffee; 
what song makes you want 
to roll the windows down 
and slam on the gas pedal. 
Find someone who takes in your smallest details; 
who notices the things 
you thought no one ever would.
And then, 
when you find them
Be their someone, too. ✨

You don't have to let the circumstances of your past negatively determine the pattern of your life in the future.
Read that again. 
And again. 
And again. ✌️

What 2022 has taught me:

Risk it all. Most chances only come once in a lifetime. 

To love and be loved by genuine people is worth more than any material or worldly accomplishment I have ever chased after or fulfilled. 

I feel more stable and fulfilled ditching hyper individualistic ideas. I don't have to go it alone, no one should. Do you feel fulfilled when you help others? Let others feel it too by allowing them to help you too.

I’ve learned to allow myself to revel in my vulnerability and flaws, to romanticize them knowing another somewhere in the world is praying for what I take for granted.

This past year taught me that healthy privacy helps you remain grounded in your truth and focused on what matters most. 

It has shown me people who love you with the purity you need want to help you the same way that you crave to help them.

It showed me I am no longer willing to participate in relationships where I have to walk on eggshells or prove myself - which is really a fear of intimacy from within. 

Instead I am committed to cultivating a divine union within as I explore intimacy through direct communication.

It reminded me to not believe everything you read or hear. Learn to trust your intuition. 

Lastly it taught me to lean into life. 
Life is only as full as you make it. 
So if you want more. 
Go get more. 
✨

Promise me that we’ll always be silly. 

That when we wake up and roll over, we’ll rub noses like little baby puppies do.  Promise me that we’ll tickle each other till we make goofy faces and than take pictures and laugh and laugh. 

Promise me that we’ll play with the skateboards in the toy aisle of the grocery store. That you’ll twirl me around in the middle of the street like we’re on the cast of some beautiful dance movie and this is our big scene. That we’ll eat ice cream sundaes in the middle of the night. And that we’ll play wrestle, and that you’ll throw me over your shoulders. 

Promise me that we’ll never grow too old or too serious.

That we’ll prank each other and lick the cake batter straight from the spoon and have water balloon fights in the middle of the summer.

We are kids. And always will be at heart.

No matter where we go or how much we grow or even where we end up five, ten, twenty years from now, please promise me that we’ll always be laughing.

I want us to tell jokes and send funny reels.  I want to poke each other and squeeze each other and drive each other crazy. I want us to blast our favorite song and scream the lyrics at the top of our lungs while we dance in the kitchen. 

I want to love you in all the ways, serious, normal, careful but especially silly.

Because if I can be silly with you, we’ll never run out of happiness. ✨

Kindness means that we recognize that others are fragile, that we have the power to hurt or heal them, and we choose to be healers. When we are kind, we don't take advantage of our power or of other people's vulnerabilities. Instead, we seek to comfort, encourage and strengthen those around us.

To be kind requires empathy: we must consciously attune ourselves to the life experience of another being to know what will feel good for them. Kindness builds confidence, because it lets us see others in all of their complicated, needy humanity, rather than putting them on pedestals.

Kindness does not ask whether it will be repaid. Even so, our kindness often ripples through the world around us; it invites others to be kind in turn.

So start today with kindness and watch how your whole world will change. ✌❤

All unhappiness is formed when we take our being away from the present moment.
Stress, disappointment and anger when we think about events of our past that we have no control over right now.
Anxiety or worry when we think about the future, also of which we have no control over right now.
Most of us seem to be always searching for some place else, some better moment in the future.
But that moment never comes.
Because when that moment comes we want more. When we just stop and appreciate everything in this moment. Everything most take for granted. 
Like the life in our bodies. 
Like the energy inside us.
Like the miracle of human life. 
Like the miracle of creation.
The wonder of this universe.
The wonder of you being able to communicate to all the parts of your body without speaking a word.
The wonder of our senses.
The sun, the rain, the air you breathe in right now.
When we can truly grasp this powerful present moment 
There are no problems
There are only miracles.
Many think being lost in the present moment might eliminate any chance of growth or success in their life.  However, the opposite is true.
When everything you do is infused with your presence, everything you do is done with more quality, with more connection, with more love.
And when you are more connected with everything you do, there is greater success on all levels.
The success all of us seek is really just the feeling we believe we will get in achieving it.
So the success itself is really a feeling.
And any feeling, even the highest elation can be achieved right now when your attention, when your appreciation is 100% focused on this perfect present moment.
When we stop seeking an end point, and instead make each moment an end in itself.
When we can appreciate the journey so much that a destination is not needed.
The journey is the new destination. The new miracle.
That is what life is really all about. Making the most out of each moment.
Appreciating the wonder and miracles in each moment.
You are complete.
As you are.
Right now.
🤍

Today’s Reminder: 
Things are not happening to you,
they are happening for you. 
Our circumstances can be our greatest teachers. 
Life can be 
overwhelming, 
exhausting, 
and frustrating some days. 
But it’s learning to step back from yourself 
and shifting your language from
“why is this happening to me?" 
to “what am I learning from this?". 
This action creates more space within yourself. When we accept the circumstance 
and let it go, 
we establish trust within ourselves 
and the Universe, Source or whatever you call the higher power.
Allow the emotions. 
Observe them 
and let them pass 
through you. 
If you allow your fears to become you, 
it will shift your perception to believing that this mere moment of lowness will last forever. 

I am here to remind you that it doesn't. 

No moment last forever. 
You need to learn to stop waiting for that perfect moment in order to have a good day. 
A moment of motivation, 
a moment of productivity, 
a moment of joy;
you're waiting for a moment 
that will never come until you decide to take action.

Practice looking within yourself to assess what you are meant to gain from the experience. 
Look at everything as an opportunity of growth. 
The ability to become the best version of yourself is worth every notion of gratitude. 
You are on the path to evolve. 
This is part of your timeline. 
Remember why you started 
and who you wish to be. 
Claim it & then become it.✨

The Law of Creation ✨
This law states that everything is created from emptiness through yin–yang interaction. Yin and yang are the two basic elements that make up everything. 
Yin and yang are 
opposite, 
relative, 
co-created, 
inseparable 
and co-dependent.
The Law of Creation gives a deeper meaning between the relationship between time and space. 
Time relates to the measurement of movement and change. 
Space relates to the measurement of stillness and solidity. 
Space and time 
are a yin–yang pair. 
Interaction of these fundamental yin–yang pairs, create our universe. 
Create our reality. 
The law underscores the importance that life doesn’t just happen to us. 
To make things happen in your life, you need to take action, instead of waiting for something to magically come your way.

You are the co-creator of making what you want, based on your intentions. 

So what are you creating? 
Do you want 
more love,
more connection, 
more purpose?

Love and connection are created in the simplest moments. 
It's never about how do we connect, 
it's about taking the time 
and creating the space 
for connection. 
It's about being present in the moments we share. 
And through presence we create our paradise 🤍

The tragedy is many of us don't know how to forgive ourselves. We get stuck in cycles of 
guilt & regret:
"I can't believe I did that."
"I can't believe how capable I am of hurting someone I love."
"I should have known better."
"I'm supposed to be so much better than this."
It's the end 
and the beginning 
of a vicious shame cycle. 
And we end up punishing ourselves by withdrawing our own love from ourselves, 
thinking that will bring justice. 
But it doesn't, does it? 
The cycle never seems to end.
Not until we compassionately and wholeheartedly forgive ourselves. 
Not an easy thing to do. 
The great news a lot of us would forgive ourselves if we knew how to. Perhaps we were never taught how to practice consciously being tender with ourselves until it becomes a habit. 
If you are capable of compassion, of releasing your feelings of anger & resentment towards another being, 
then you are capable of being compassionate towards yourself. 
Forgiveness sets you free.
And there is justice from learning from your mistakes 
and becoming free.
You are not stuck; 
you have been granted the opportunity to know better, 
to grow, 
to live in alignment 
with who you actually 
want to be. ✨

You’re an original, 
an individual, 
a masterpiece. 
Celebrate it! 
Don’t let your uniqueness make you shy. 
Don’t be someone other than the wonder you are.  Everyone has their own dreams, 
their own struggles, 
and a different path that makes sense for them. 
You are you for a reason. 
Own it.
✨

All unhappiness is formed when we take our 
being away from the present moment.
Stress,

and anger 
when we think about events of our past that we have no control over right now.
Anxiety or worry when we think about the future, also of which we have no control over right now.
Most of us seem to be always searching for some place else, some better moment in the future.
But that moment never comes.
Because when that moment comes we want more.  When we just stop and appreciate everything in this moment. 
Everything most take for granted. Like the life in our bodies. 
Like the energy inside us.
Like the miracle of human life. Like the miracle of creation.
The wonder of this universe.
The wonder of you being able to communicate to all the parts of your body without speaking a word.
The wonder of our senses.
The sun, the rain, the air you breathe in right now.
When we can truly grasp this powerful present moment,
There are no problems

Many think being lost in the present moment might eliminate any chance of growth or success in their life.  However, the opposite is true.
When everything you do is infused with your presence, everything you do is done

with more connection,

with everything you do, 
there is greater success on all levels.
The success all of us seek is really just 
the feeling we believe we will get in achieving it.

And any feeling, even the highest elation can be achieved 
right now 
when your attention, 
when your appreciation is 
100% focused on the 
present moment.
When we stop seeking an end point, 
and instead make each moment an end in itself.
When we can appreciate the journey 
so much that a destination is not needed.
The journey is the new destination. 
The new miracle.
That is what life is really all about. Making the most out of each moment
Appreciating the wonder 
and miracles in each moment.
You need nothing materially speaking.
You are complete.
As you are

I can’t change the past, 
but I can effect my future.

Really stepping back today. 
Changing my perspective. 
Perception. 
Working on my ability 
to let go long enough
to move forward. 
It’s believing with blind faith 
that when you let go, 
that release will allow what is ahead of you 
to move into your life. 
That it will allow what is waiting for you 
to have its place. 
You allow yourself to receive more. 
In letting go you create space. 
Think of this physically. 
In order to clean up, you need to let go. 
You remove the old to make room for the new. 
In the sense of straightening your home 
it seems so simple. 
Toss the old, 
give away what can be used by others, 
repurpose that which still has a place in your life. 
The same goes for your life. 
To create space for something new 
we need to let go of the old. 
Be ok with that it had an important space in our life but that now it’s time to move forward. 
Recognizing that space between something adding to our lives and something draining our lives. 
It’s such a fine line. 
And only we have the answers for ourselves. 
They always lie within. 
So sometimes to find the answers within. 
You need to step back. 
Access the big picture. 
Stop looking at every pixel 
and appreciate the entire picture. 
This allows you to discern better 
as to what needs to go. And what can stay. 
Then what I’m learning is to detach from the things that no longer serve me with love. 
Detach with love. 
Say it again. 
That’s the hard part. 
Easier to recognize, harder to practice. 
But that’s exactly what it is, it’s practice. 
Every time I find myself in a situation of letting go I do a lot of personal inventories. 
Constantly evaluating when I am in the process and drawing attentions to the 
feelings, 
emotions, 
and behaviors attached to the process. 
I practice being mindful and intentional in the process therefore the next time I experience a similar situation, I can use the empowerment of knowing I survived my previous experience. 
This drives me forward with hope for the future. Turning my thoughts from frustration to proactive positivity.

In the Northern Hemisphere the Winter Solstice occurs when the sun is at its southernmost or lowest point in the sky. It is the longest night/shortest day of the year. Solstice literally translates as “sun stands still”, which is what it appears to do for 3 days from the Solstice before it starts to move northwards once more, bringing with it the light. 
While our predecessors honored the sun for its provision of safety, security and heat they also recognized the Winter Solstice as the birth of the spiritual sun within, the inner spiritual aspect or the “soul spark” being reborn. 
Today’s your rebirth,
stop and enjoy it’s moments ✨

Being a mother is a gift that is unimaginable. It’s a connection that is unmatched and insurmountable in any form or other relationship. It’s a love that grows continually, a love that always wants more and better. It’s being terrified that you can’t prevent pain, injustice and heartbreak. It’s laughing at jokes that aren’t even funny, but the way they say it makes it’s hilarious. It’s listening to stories that go on and on without a point. It’s always being available for the “Mother watch me!” yells and “Mother I need you” please. It’s drowning out the word Mom repeated over and over in attempts to get your attention. It’s songs sang out of tune and settling squabbles with siblings. It’s being mean, and teaching hard lessons, that hurt you inside so deep you want to cry, but you must stand strong with resolve. It’s being strong for them when you are weak. It’s smiling when you want to cry, and crying when you’re smiling with pride. It’s confusion, mistakes, uncharted territory and blindfolded guessing. It’s snuggling on the couch watching a movie, braiding hair till your fingers hurt, it’s being woken up early on Saturday morning because they want to crawl in bed and be close to your heart. It’s having the worst day and having them hug you and tell you “Mother, I love you”, and needing nothing more.
It’s a blessing, a gift, a relationship that never ends and a love that never dies. It’s the best thing I have ever become, the greatest love I have ever felt and the best part about being me.
